WIZARD COMMANDS
GAUGE
The syntax is ~CCOMgauge <command>~CHLP. It runs the command as normal, then returns the evaluation cost of the last executed command and its execution time in seconds.

For example, ~CCOMgauge grep LOOK /*~CHLP gives the following results:

 ~CDEFtags:ERQ_HANDLE_RLOOKUP include/erq.h   49;"    d
 <snip several matches>
 tags:LOOK       include/const/varconst.h        6;"     d
 grep LOOK /*:
    Eval Cost: 79634
    Real Time: 1.072666 seconds~CHLP
